AGI - Next week Matteo Falcinelli and his mother, Vlasta, will leave Miami and return to Italy. The 25-year-old son, enrolled in a master's degree at Florida International University, is at the center of an investigation initiated by the prosecutor of Rome who wants to ascertain the facts that led to the arrest by the Miami police of the boy, stopped at the exit of a stripclub, handcuffed and tortured, as documented by the shocking images taken from the body-cam of the agents.
&nbsp;
The family asks for justice. In the coming hours the police and administration of North Miami should issue a statement about the case.&nbsp;Matteo, footballer, athletic boy and described as solar, who in the United States graduated in business administration and management at wesleyan University, in North Carolina, should conclude his studies in Florida in the spring of 2025, six months more than expected, due to trauma related to the experience with the police. In the video some images of Matteo, made available to the media by the family, since he was a child a day of graduation in the USA, and with his mother, Vlasta, who reached him in Miami and who follows the whole story.
