AGI -&nbsp;With 143 votes in favour, 9 against and 25 abstentions, the United Nations General Assembly approves the resolution which supports the request of Palestine to enter the United Nations as a member of all effects. Italy has abstained.<br> A long applause of the court welcomed the result. The resolution calls on the Security Council, the only body capable of making the resolution effective, to "reconsider the matter favorably". &nbsp;
&nbsp;
Among the twenty-five member countries of the United Nations who abstained in the vote of the General Assembly who had to decide whether to accept the request of Palestine to enter as a full member, in addition to Italy are Canada, United Kingdom, Germany, Holland, Romania, Sweden, Finland and Ukraine. They voted in favour, among others, France and Spain. The resolution, which needs the free way of the Security Council, was adopted with 143 si', 9 no and 25 astenuti.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
&nbsp; Italy has declared itself in favour of the solution "two peoples two states" to resolve the crisis in the Middle East but considers that the "solution must be reached through direct negotiations between Israel and Palestine". The ambassador to the UN Maurizio Massari, during his speech at the General Assembly, declared this, where the resolution was adopted to accept the request of Palestine to join the UN in full. &nbsp;
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
<h2> Israel scraps the Charter of the United Nations
"With today's vote, not only bypass the Security Council in violation of the Charter, but embalm the meaning of peace lovers." The ambassador of Israel to the UN, Gilad Erdan, said this in his speech to the United Nations General Assembly, which is preparing to vote for the approval of the entry of Palestine as a member of all effects. Israel is against the admission of Palestinians. The Israeli ambassador concluded his intervention by passing through the paper cutter the founding Charter of the United Nations. "Vergognate", Erdan said before leaving the stage.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<h2> Reactions in Italy
<h3>Schlein, entry Palestine
&nbsp;"We have now arrived the very positive news that at the UN they approved the entry of Palestine as a member to all effects. For us that we have been calling for the ceasefire and to resume a path of peace which points to the political solution for two peoples and two states is an important step forward. The Palestinian people are not Hamas." It says the segertaria del Pd, Elly Schlein, in Pesaro.
"To isolate Hamas we must not crush the legitimate aspiration of the Palestinians to have a state in which to live in peace and security. Just like Israel. So we will continue to fight for peace," he added.
&nbsp;
<h3> Contract, abstention in contradiction with parliament
"Why did Italy abstain on the membership of Palestine at the United Nations? A choice in open contradiction with the vote of the Parliament of 2015 when a motion for the recognition of the State of Palestine was approved. A cynical decision by Meloni." He writes on social media the parent Pd in the House Work Committee, Arturo Scotto.
&nbsp;
<h3>M5s, shameful abstention
"Today Melonian Italy has demonstrated its true face for the umpteenth time, with yet another shameful abstention on the historic resolution adopted today, with massive vote, of the General Assembly of the United Nations, which has given way to the accession of Palestine to the UN as a full member. Countries such as France and Spain voted in favour, while Italy has passively aligned with the United States and the United Kingdom. An unworthy position because it was a highly symbolic vote that falls at a dramatic time, with the tanks of Netanyahu pointing their guns against Rafah. The 5 Star Movement condemns this vote, given not in the name of Italy that believes in peace, not in our name". The 5 Star Movement of Chamber and Senate Foreign Commissions declare this.
